article.description: Eastern Illinois rallies past Tennessee State 64-57
article.headline: Eastern Illinois rallies past Tennessee State 64-57
article.linkText: Eastern Illinois rallies past Tennessee State 64-57
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Chris Olivier scored 14 points off the bench, hitting a pair of free throws late and then blocking a shot as Eastern Illinois rallied in the second half to defeat Tennessee State 64-57 on Wednesday night, rising to 3-0 in the Ohio Valley Conference for the first time. The Panthers (9-6, 3-0) fashioned a 14-3 run late in the second half to claw back from a 12-point deficit to win its sixth-straight. Reggie Smith hit a jumper and a 3-pointer to spark the run, Josh Piper added a 3-pointer to close to 47-44 after a pair of Olivier free throws. Luke Piotrowski knotted the score at 47 and Cornell Johnston drained a 3-pointer as the Panthers led 50-47. Johnston scored 12 for Eastern Illinois, Piper 11 with 10 boards. Olivier had two of his three blocked shots in the last 2:14. Darreon Reddick led the Tigers (3-14, 0-2) with 13 points.
